{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"One day, Los Angeles Times columnist"},{"time":3000,"text":"Steve Lopez was walking along"},{"time":5000,"text":"the streets of downtown Los Angeles"},{"time":7000,"text":"when he heard beautiful music."},{"time":10000,"text":"And the source was a man,"},{"time":12000,"text":"an African-American man,"},{"time":14000,"text":"charming, rugged, homeless,"},{"time":18000,"text":"playing a violin that only had two strings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"And I'm telling a story that many of you know,"},{"time":23000,"text":"because Steve's columns became the basis"},{"time":26000,"text":"for a book, which was turned into a movie,"},{"time":29000,"text":"with Robert Downey Jr. acting as Steve Lopez,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and Jamie Foxx as Nathaniel Anthony Ayers,"},{"time":34000,"text":"the Juilliard-trained double bassist"},{"time":36000,"text":"whose promising career was cut short"},{"time":39000,"text":"by a tragic affliction with paranoid schizophrenia."},{"time":43000,"text":"Nathaniel dropped out of Juilliard, he suffered a complete breakdown,"},{"time":45000,"text":"and 30 years later he was living homeless"},{"time":47000,"text":"on the streets of Skid Row in downtown Los Angeles."},{"time":51000,"text":"I encourage all of you to read Steve's book or to watch the movie"},{"time":54000,"text":"to understand not only the beautiful bond"},{"time":57000,"text":"that formed between these two men,"},{"time":59000,"text":"but how music helped shape that bond,"},{"time":62000,"text":"and ultimately was instrumental -- if you'll pardon the pun --"},{"time":65000,"text":"in helping Nathaniel get off the streets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"I met Mr. Ayers in 2008,"},{"time":71000,"text":"two years ago, at Walt Disney Concert Hall."},{"time":73000,"text":"He had just heard a performance of Beethoven's First and Fourth symphonies,"},{"time":76000,"text":"and came backstage and introduced himself."},{"time":78000,"text":"He was speaking in a very jovial and gregarious way"},{"time":81000,"text":"about Yo-Yo Ma and Hillary Clinton"},{"time":84000,"text":"and how the Dodgers were never going to make the World Series,"},{"time":86000,"text":"all because of the treacherous first violin passage work"},{"time":89000,"text":"in the last movement of Beethoven's Fourth Symphony."},{"time":93000,"text":"And we got talking about music, and I got an email from Steve a few days later"},{"time":97000,"text":"saying that Nathaniel was interested in a violin lesson with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"Now, I should mention that Nathaniel refuses treatment"},{"time":104000,"text":"because when he was treated it was with shock therapy"},{"time":107000,"text":"and Thorazine and handcuffs,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and that scar has stayed with him for his entire life."},{"time":113000,"text":"But as a result now, he is prone to"},{"time":115000,"text":"these schizophrenic episodes,"},{"time":117000,"text":"the worst of which can manifest themselves as"},{"time":119000,"text":"him exploding"},{"time":121000,"text":"and then disappearing for days,"},{"time":123000,"text":"wandering the streets of Skid Row,"},{"time":125000,"text":"exposed to its horrors, with the torment of his own mind"},{"time":129000,"text":"unleashed upon him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"And Nathaniel was in such a state of agitation"},{"time":134000,"text":"when we started our first lesson at Walt Disney Concert Hall --"},{"time":137000,"text":"he had a kind of manic glint in his eyes,"},{"time":140000,"text":"he was lost."},{"time":142000,"text":"And he was talking about"},{"time":144000,"text":"invisible demons and smoke,"},{"time":146000,"text":"and how someone was poisoning him in his sleep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"And I was afraid,"},{"time":152000,"text":"not for myself, but I was afraid"},{"time":155000,"text":"that I was going to lose him,"},{"time":157000,"text":"that he was going to sink into one of his states,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and that I would ruin his relationship with the violin"},{"time":162000,"text":"if I started talking about scales"},{"time":164000,"text":"and arpeggios and other exciting forms of"},{"time":166000,"text":"didactic violin pedagogy."},{"time":168000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":169000,"text":"So, I just started playing."},{"time":172000,"text":"And I played the first movement of the Beethoven Violin Concerto."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"And as I played,"},{"time":178000,"text":"I understood that there was a profound change"},{"time":181000,"text":"occurring in Nathaniel's eyes."},{"time":183000,"text":"It was as if he was in the grip of some invisible pharmaceutical,"},{"time":186000,"text":"a chemical reaction, for which my playing the music"},{"time":190000,"text":"was its catalyst."},{"time":193000,"text":"And Nathaniel's manic rage"},{"time":197000,"text":"was transformed into understanding,"},{"time":201000,"text":"a quiet curiosity and grace."},{"time":206000,"text":"And in a miracle, he lifted his own violin"},{"time":209000,"text":"and he started playing, by ear,"},{"time":212000,"text":"certain snippets of violin concertos"},{"time":214000,"text":"which he then asked me to complete -- Mendelssohn,"},{"time":216000,"text":"Tchaikovsky, Sibelius."},{"time":218000,"text":"And we started talking about music, from Bach"},{"time":220000,"text":"to Beethoven and Brahms,"},{"time":222000,"text":"Bruckner, all the B's,"},{"time":224000,"text":"from Bart√≥k, all the way up to Esa-Pekka Salonen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"And I understood that he not only"},{"time":228000,"text":"had an encyclopedic knowledge of music,"},{"time":230000,"text":"but he related to this music at a personal level."},{"time":234000,"text":"He spoke about it with the kind of passion"},{"time":236000,"text":"and understanding that I share with my colleagues"},{"time":238000,"text":"in the Los Angeles Philharmonic."},{"time":241000,"text":"And through playing music and talking about music,"},{"time":244000,"text":"this man had transformed"},{"time":246000,"text":"from the paranoid, disturbed man"},{"time":249000,"text":"that had just come from walking the streets"},{"time":251000,"text":"of downtown Los Angeles"},{"time":253000,"text":"to the charming, erudite,"},{"time":255000,"text":"brilliant, Juilliard-trained musician."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"Music is medicine. Music changes us."},{"time":264000,"text":"And for Nathaniel, music is sanity."},{"time":268000,"text":"Because music allows him to take his thoughts"},{"time":270000,"text":"and delusions and shape them"},{"time":273000,"text":"through his imagination and his creativity,"},{"time":275000,"text":"into reality."},{"time":277000,"text":"And that is an escape"},{"time":279000,"text":"from his tormented state."},{"time":281000,"text":"And I understood that this was the very essence of art."},{"time":284000,"text":"This was the very reason why we made music,"},{"time":286000,"text":"that we take something that exists within all of us"},{"time":288000,"text":"at our very fundamental core,"},{"time":290000,"text":"our emotions,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and through our artistic lens,"},{"time":294000,"text":"through our creativity, we're able to shape those emotions into reality."},{"time":299000,"text":"And the reality of that expression"},{"time":301000,"text":"reaches all of us"},{"time":303000,"text":"and moves us, inspires and unites us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"And for Nathaniel,"},{"time":310000,"text":"music brought him back into a fold of friends."},{"time":313000,"text":"The redemptive power of music brought him back"},{"time":315000,"text":"into a family of musicians"},{"time":317000,"text":"that understood him,"},{"time":319000,"text":"that recognized his talents"},{"time":321000,"text":"and respected him."},{"time":324000,"text":"And I will always make music with Nathaniel,"},{"time":327000,"text":"whether we're at Walt Disney Concert Hall"},{"time":329000,"text":"or on Skid Row, because he reminds me"},{"time":331000,"text":"why I became a musician."},{"time":334000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":336000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you. Thanks."},{"time":346000,"text":"Robert Gupta."},{"time":348000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"Robert Gupta: I'm going to play something that I shamelessly stole from cellists."},{"time":370000,"text":"So, please forgive me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":373000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":538000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}